{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Researchers unveiled an interactive tool showing that any significant change would have to involve action by the states and reduced sentences for violent offenders.", "abstract": "The Upshot; Urban Institute has created interactive online feature that allows users to gauge effectiveness of various proposed policy changes at state level on size of prison populations; feature underscores challenges facing criminal justice reform and issue of large number of incarcerated Americans, and points to fissures in bipartisan support for idea, particularly with respect to sentencing reform on state-by-state basis.", "section_name": "The Upshot", "print_page": "3", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Erik", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ECKHOLM", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By ERIK ECKHOLM"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/12/upshot/how-to-cut-the-prison-population-see-for-yourself.html", "lead_paragraph": "Researchers unveiled an interactive tool showing that any significant change would have to involve action by the states and reduced sentences for violent offenders.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Tests for Reducing Prison Populations", "main": "How to Cut the Prison Population (See for Yourself)", "content_kicker": "Incarceration Nation", "kicker": "The Upshot"}, "_id": "55c9d5c238f0d87d6b06f3d1", "word_count": "1039", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/08/12/upshot/12UP-prisons/12UP-prisons-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/08/12/upshot/12UP-prisons/12UP-prisons-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 376, "url": "images/2015/08/12/upshot/12UP-prisons/12UP-prisons-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/08/12/upshot/12UP-prisons/12UP-prisons-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "376"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "typ